------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
INSTALL
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  1.) Install from Kali/OpenVAS repos 
  2.) Install from source 
  3.) run from a docker container (Preferred Method)

3a.) apt install docker.io

3b.) docker run -d -p 443:443 --name openvas mikesplain/openvas
          
          "This will pull & run the docker container
          
3c.) Navigate to "https://127.0.0.1"  credentials "admin/admin"

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Initial Config..
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
.) Navigating to "SCANS > TASKS" and click on the purple magic wand icon to begin the basic configuration wizard

      Note: Initially scan your localhost to ensure everything is properly configured "127.0.0.1"
      
.) Dashboard will appear for monitoring and analyzing your complete and ongoing scans

.) After scan finishes Navigate to "SCANS > REPORTS" and click on newly created report

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Basic TASK Creation 
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
.) Goto "SCANS >TASKS" to create a new scan

.) Navigate to the star icon (upper right-hand corner of the Tasks dashboard) & select "NEW TASK" 

.) Name, Scan Targets, and Scanner Type, and Scan Config

    Name: Allows us to set the name of the scan
    Scan Targets: The targets to scan can include Hosts, Ports, & Credentials
    Scanner: The scanner by default will be OpenVAS architecture BUT you can set this to any scanner in the settings menu
    Scan Config: OpenVAS has 7 different scan types is based on how aggressive or what information you want to collect from your scan

Scoping a New Target:
---------------------
    
.) Navigate to the star icon next to "SCAN TARGETS"

.) The two main options you will need to configure are the "NAME" & "HOSTS". Other options will only be used in advanced vulnerability management solutions

.) Now the TARGET is scoped continue to create task and begin the scan

.)Once you create the task you will be brought back to the scan dashboard where you can monitor and start your task

.)To start the task navigate to the start icon under Actions and press Green Play Button

